title: Fantasm Pick Case
description:
Fantasm Industries didn't come here to whisper.

This lime green Phantom case is built like it owes you money and wants to make things right. We're talking 1000D Cordura, mil-spec everything, PALS webbing that could probably survive a small explosion. It's the kind of overkill that makes you nod approvingly while stuffing it full of picks.
descriptionContinued:
- Inside: 20 pockets that actually fit the handles you own (yeah, even those chunky 44 Delta boys), plus a full-width zippered pocket for all your tension tools and "I swear I'll use this someday" gear. Velcro fields on the inside and outside mean you can slap whatever patches represent your personal brand of chaos.

- Outside: Carry handles, D-rings for hanging or strapping, and enough visibility that you'll never lose this thing. Seriously. You could drop it in a forest and find it from space.

- This case holds its shape when loaded, carries comfortably, and looks like it escaped from a highlighter factory.

- Tools not included. Bad decisions optional. Fantasm Industries builds stuff for people who actually use it.
potContents: 1x [Phantom Case](https://fantasmindustries.com/products/phantom-lock-pick-case-mil-spec-build) in lime/neon green

There is also a range of different material options for both the outside and inside, from really nice real cork fabric to velvet like materials.

title: Pick the Rainbow
description: While this box may look just exactly like a very ordinary box of Skittles, the truth is that in addition to actual Skittles, this nearly 10-pound pot from the end of the rainbow also contains some cleverly hidden secrets that will last you far longer than any other Skittles you'll ever come across!
descriptionContinued:
Be choosy about which ones you put in your mouth; the big ones are too large to comfortably fit, and they won't do your teeth any favors! Some people may enjoy these by blindly taking one at random, but others will find it more pleasing to line them up like an OCD person and methodically complete one color before moving on to the next. I personally found each of these to be a good experience and would recommend this pot for a beginner to intermediate picker looking for a broad experience ascending the ranks.

- 1 Rosengrens 32a81
- 1 Robur 2391

title: The Nameless Lock Project Prototype
description: A one-of-a-kind, all brass, cube shaped padlock and key. The result of community input and countless hours of design work toward an outrageous lock. Please note: this project is ongoing and the prototype is still being worked on as of this listing. Digs is racing to finish this lock by the time the RAFL goes live for contributions, but it is likely you will need to wait to receive your prize.
potContents: - Prototype padlock from the "Nameless Lock Project"
